article.headline: Central Connecticut 77, St. Francis, N.Y. 64
article.story: NEW BRITAIN, Conn. (AP) -- Tristan Blackwood had 26 points to lead Central Connecticut to a 77-64 win over winless St. Francis of New York on Wednesday. Javier Mojica added 22 points and 11 rebounds for the Blue Devils (2-4). Robert Hines led the Terriers (0-7) with 19 points and seven rebounds. St. Francis opened quickly with 12-5 run, but Central took the lead with a 10-0 run midway through the first half. The Terriers were held without a field goal for more than eight minutes before a layup by Robert Hines cut CCSUs lead to 22-16. The Blue Devils closed the half with six straight points to take a 34-23 lead at the break. The Terriers put together a 6-2 rally early in the second half when Central's leading rebounder, Obie Nwadike, picked up his fourth foul at the 18:09. But Mojica led the Blue Devils on a 12-3 run over a span of just under three minutes that put the game out of reach. Central led by as many as 22 down the stretch.
